Statefull
Ingress works at Layer-7 and is used for HTTP/HTTPS applications like web apps, REST APIs, and dashboards, but not for databases or TCP-based systems.

| Pattern      | Session Stored | DB Needed   | Ingress Sticky |
| ------------ | -------------- | ---------   | -------------- |
| Pod-Stateful | Pod RAM / PVC  | âŒ No      | âœ… Yes         |
| DB-Stateful  | DB / Redis     | âœ… Yes     | âŒ No          |
| Hybrid       | Both           | âœ… Yes     | Optional       |

There are three Types of Stateful application

1ï¸âƒ£ Pod-Stateful Application (NO DB for session)
ğŸ“Œ What this means
Session stored in pod memory or pod PVC
Same user â†’ same pod (sticky session)

Real-World Examples
User logs in
Session stored in:
Pod memory (RAM) or
Pod PVC (disk)
Same user must always hit same pod

2ï¸âƒ£ DB-Stateful Application (MOST COMMON TODAY)
ğŸ“Œ What this means
Session & data stored outside pod
Pods are stateless
Any pod can serve any user

Example 1: E-commerce (Amazon / Flipkart-like)
Login
Cart
Orders

3ï¸âƒ£ Hybrid Stateful Application (FAST + SAFE)
ğŸ“Œ What this means
Some state in memory
Some state in DB
Performance + durability

Example 1: Trading Platforms (Zerodha-like)
Active trades â†’ memory
Account balance â†’ DB

Example 2: Online Gaming Backends
Live game session â†’ memory
Player stats â†’ DB

What is Redis? (Simple Definition)
Redis is a very fast, in-memory data store used to store temporary data like sessions, cache, and counters.
Databases are:
Slow compared to memory
Expensive to query repeatedly

Redis:
Stores data in RAM
Extremely fast
Used for data that changes frequently
ex- 
1ï¸âƒ£ User Session Data (MOST COMMON)
Why changes frequently?
Every request updates session info (last activity, auth token, etc.)
Example
key: session:user123
value: {
  "userId": 123,
  "isLoggedIn": true,
  "lastAccess": "2026-01-09T18:10:00"
}
TTL: 30 minutes

Real use case
Login system
Kubernetes pods are stateless
Redis keeps user logged in even if pod changes

2ï¸âƒ£ Shopping Cart Data
Why changes frequently?
Add item âŒ remove item âŒ update quantity âŒ
Example
key: cart:user123
value: {
  "items": [
    {"productId": 101, "qty": 2},
    {"productId": 205, "qty": 1}
  ]
}
Real use case
Amazon / Flipkart
Cart should be fast
Not stored in DB until checkout

3ï¸âƒ£ OTP / Verification Codes
Why changes frequently?
OTP is generated, verified, and expired quickly
Example
key: otp:9876543210
value: 483921
TTL: 120 seconds

Real use case
Login OTP
Password reset
2FA

