ğŸ§  How can you achieve zero downtime in Kubernetes?
  We can achieve zero downtime in Kubernetes through RollingUpdate strategy. 

MONITERING
Monitoring tells you WHAT is happening in your system.
Examples of Metrics
CPU usage = 70%
Memory usage = 1.2 GB
Request count = 500 req/sec
Error rate = 2%
Response time = 200 ms
EX-
Prometheus â†’ collects metrics
Grafana â†’ visualizes metrics (dashboards)
Kiali â†’ shows traffic, errors, latency (Istio)

LOGGING 
Logging tells you WHAT exactly happened and WHY.
Monitoring shows error rate = 5%
Logs show:
ERROR: Database connection timeout
ğŸ“„ Logging tells you:
â€œError happened because DB connection failedâ€

